SKILL|apple-reminders|"Apple Reminders via remindctl: add, list, complete."
STEP|1|**macOS** with Reminders.app
STEP|2|Install: `brew install steipete/tap/remindctl`
STEP|3|Grant Reminders permission when prompted
STEP|4|Check: `remindctl status` / Request: `remindctl authorize`
STEP|5|User mentions "reminder" or "Reminders app"
STEP|6|Creating personal to-dos with due dates that sync to iOS
STEP|7|Managing Apple Reminders lists
STEP|8|User wants tasks to appear on their iPhone/iPad
STEP|9|Scheduling agent alerts → use the cronjob tool instead
STEP|10|Calendar events → use Apple Calendar or Google Calendar
STEP|11|Project task management → use GitHub Issues, Notion, etc.
STEP|12|If user says "remind me" but means an agent alert → clarify first
STEP|13|`--due` sets the reminder's due date/time.
STEP|14|`--alarm` sets the EventKit alarm/notification trigger. Timed due reminders may default to an alarm at the due time, but pass `--alarm` explicitly when the user asks for an earlier nudge.
STEP|15|`dueDate`: actual due time
STEP|16|`alarmDate`: notification / early nudge time
STEP|17|`today`, `tomorrow`, `yesterday`
STEP|18|`YYYY-MM-DD`
STEP|19|`YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm`
STEP|20|ISO 8601 (`2026-01-04T12:34:56Z`)
STEP|21|When user says "remind me", clarify: Apple Reminders (syncs to phone) vs agent cronjob alert
STEP|22|Always confirm reminder content and due date before creating
STEP|23|Use `--json` for programmatic parsing
PIT|**macOS** with Reminders.app
